dfischer.utils

Class MD5

  • java.lang.Object
    • dfischer.utils.MD5

  • public class MD5
extends java.lang.Object
    Implementation of the MD5 algorithm. Allows calculating checksums.
    See also RFC 1321.

    After the object has been created by its constructor the method calc() must be executed. The resulting checksum result can read with getregs() or toString(). Programming example:

     MD5 md5 = new MD5("inputString");
 md5.calc();
 String result = md5.toString();

      • calcStackTrace

        public static java.lang.String calcStackTrace(java.lang.Throwable t)
        Calculates the checksum of a Java stack trace. Note: first, from an exception or an error the stack trace is generated in ASCII text format. After that the checksum is calculated by using the ASCII text of the stack trace.
        Parameters:
        t - the Error or Exception from which the checksum of the stack trace is calculated
        Returns:
        the checksum of the stack trace
